  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/257",
  "title": "test(stack): use jsdom for unit testing",
  "body": "Basically I switched to jsdom because:\n- mocha cannot show nice diffs when assertions throws (https://gi\n  hub.com/mochajs/mocha/issues/1348)\n- karma + mocha can be really slow\n- you should only need a real browser in unit testing when debugging\n  weird stuff, so you have now npm run `test:watch:browser`\n- integration testing will handle the \"multi browser test\"\n\nI also added expect.toEqualJSX to get nice diffs.\n\nSome before/after:\n\nbefore:\n\n> npm test (11.5s)\n> ![2015-10-16-102143_784x375_scrot](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/123822/10537209/88da8224-73f0-11e5-8a00-c071d8b3e5a1.png)\n\nafter:\n\n> npm test (4.5s)\n> ![2015-10-16-102109_765x398_scrot](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/123822/10537219/99b58530-73f0-11e5-9575-7c1806d42d21.png)\n\nbefore:\n\n> JSX failure in npm test\n> ![2015-10-16-102450_1037x566_scrot](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/123822/10537231/acd33c48-73f0-11e5-921a-41c55fe13875.png)\n\nafter:\n\n> JSX failure in npm test\n> ![2015-10-16-102602_760x613_scrot](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/123822/10537237/b53b8d2c-73f0-11e5-8a14-88c25bae336e.png)\n",
